White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki held a press briefing aboard Air Force One en route to Chester, Pennsylvania. She discussed various topics, including the Biden administration's visit to Smith Flooring, a black-owned union shop that received Paycheck Protection Program loans and qualifies for additional programs under the American Rescue Plan. Psaki also addressed North Korea's recent comments, stating that the administration's focus is on working with partners and allies to ensure security in the Korean Peninsula. She responded to questions about infrastructure, the COVID-19 vaccine rollout, Republican lawmakers' reluctance to get vaccinated, upcoming diplomatic meetings with China and Russia, and the President's plans for a press conference. Psaki mentioned that the President wants to increase the refugee cap and make the Child Tax Credit permanent, but discussions with Congress are ongoing. She also provided updates on the National Cyber Director role and the President's meeting with the Taoiseach of Ireland.